  "prompt": "The differences between adverbs and adjectives.?",
  "response": "Here are the key differences between adverbs and adjectives:\n\nAdjectives:\n1. Describe or modify nouns and pronouns\n2. Answer questions like \"What kind?\" or \"Which one?\"\n3. Typically appear before nouns or after linking verbs\n4. Examples: beautiful, happy, tall, red\n\nExamples:\n- A happy child\n- The red car\n- She seems happy\n\nAdverbs:\n1. Describe or modify verbs, adjectives, or other adverbs\n2. Answer questions like \"How?\", \"When?\", \"Where?\", or \"To what extent?\"\n3. Often end in \"-ly\"\n4. Can appear in various positions in a sentence\n\nExamples:\n- She sings beautifully\n- He ran quickly\n- They arrived late\n\nKey Distinctions:\n- Adjectives describe things/people\n- Adverbs describe actions/qualities\n- Adjectives modify nouns\n- Adverbs modify verbs, adjectives, or other adverbs\n\nConversion:\nMany adjectives can be converted to adverbs by adding \"-ly\":\n- Quick (adjective) \u2192 Quickly (adverb)\n- Careful (adjective) \u2192 Carefully (adverb)\n\nUnderstanding these differences helps in using language more precisely.",
